rs_graph_processing repo already linked from the original README. So every
new script's `--data-root` points at that external derived-data tree, not
at this repo's Timeseries/ folder -- documented explicitly in the new
README so the pipeline isn't misleading about what it can run out of the
box with just what's committed.

Four real bugs/gaps were found in the source notebooks and confirmed with
the user before fixing (via AskUserQuestion) rather than guessed at
silently, since this backs a published preprint:
1. The HDI "kappa" CSVs (kappas_degree.csv etc.) were read in 6+ places but
   never actually written anywhere -- the only candidate save cells were
   commented out and referenced an undefined variable. User chose:
   reconstruct a real save step (scripts/hdi/compute_hdi.py), inferred from
   the surrounding (working) per-subject LinearRegression logic.
2. CCML's visualization step imported a local `PlotFunction` module (via a
   hardcoded sys.path into a course-tutorial folder) that doesn't exist
   anywhere in the repo. User chose: write a reasonable reconstruction
   (scripts/ccml/plot_utils.py, scatter_2d), documented as a reconstruction
   not the original.
3. CCML was fully implemented (embedding + permutation test) for
   'degree'/'closeness' but only had the data-prep half for 'clustering'.
   User chose: complete clustering by mirroring the other two metrics
   (scripts/ccml/run_ccml.py).
4. Two different survey CSV filenames were used across the behavior
   analyses. User confirmed this is intentional (not a naming-drift bug) --
   kept as two distinct default paths, both overridable via CLI.
Also fixed without asking (unambiguous naming bugs, not scientific
judgment calls): the nodal-metrics writer saved degree centrality under
column "Degree" while every downstream reader (HDI, CCML) expected
"Degree_centrality" -- standardized on "Degree_centrality" everywhere. Also
fixed a ROI->network typo ('Occipial_R' -> 'Occipital_R') in the chord-plot
